

                    // Encapsulation

    The process of Grouping up of data members and member functions into a single unit is called as Encapsulation.

    every java class is an example of Encapsulation.

    Any Component which satisfies Data Hiding and Abstraction is also an Component of Encapsulation.


    Advantages of Encapsulation.                                DisAdvantages

    Security                                                    Reduces Performance
    Code readability/Manageability/Modularity                   Increases Code size.


            // Tightly Encapsulated Class

    If all the variables present in the class are declared as private, then such a class is called as Tightly Encapsulated Class.


